Group¶

class alfred3_interact.group.Group(matchmaker, **kwargs)[source]¶

Bases: object

The group object holds members and keeps track of their roles.

The group object’s main task is providing access to the group members via their roles. Most importantly, the group offers the attributes me and you. Beyond that, you can use dot notation, using any member’s role like an attribute on the group. The group will return a GroupMember object for the member inhabiting that role:

import alfred3 as al
from alfred3_interact import MatchMaker

exp = al.Experiment()

@exp.setup
def setup(exp):
    mm = MatchMaker("a", "b", exp=exp)
    exp.plugins.group = mm.match_stepwise()
    print(exp.plugins.group.a) # Accessing the GroupMember with role "a"

exp += al.Page(name="demo")

See also

For more details, refer to the MatchMaker documentation.

Methods

active_members

Iterator: A generator, iterating over all active members of the group.

active_or_finished_members

chat

Shortcut for creating a group chat.

get_member_by_id

GroupMember: Returns the GroupMember belonging to the experiment session with session id id.

get_member_by_role

GroupMember: Returns the GroupMember that inhabits the given role.

members

Iterator: A generator, iterating over all members of the group.

ongoing_roles

Iterator: Iterates over roles for which sessions are currently in progess.

open_roles

Iterator: Iterates over open roles (str).

other_members

Iterator: A generator, iterating over the active group members except for me.

Attributes

DATA_TYPE

full

Indicates whether the group is full or not.

me

GroupMember object for the own session.

path

Path to group data file in offline group experiments.

shared_data

Gives access to the group’s shared data dictionary, which will always automatically synchronize data for all group members.

you

GroupMember object for the other participant in a dyad (i.e.
